Argentine Stocks: Banco Macro, Ledesma, Petrobras Argentina

-- B y   B r y a n   G i b e l
-- 
2011-08-02T20:50:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-02/argentine-stocks-banco-macro-bbva-banco-frances-ledesma-saai.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 4:14 p.m. New York time.  The Merval Index fell 0.6 percent to 3,316.48.  Banco Macro SA (BMA)  ,  Argentina ’s largest lender by
market value, slid 3.4 percent to 14.40 pesos. The price of
Argentine dollar-denominated  government bonds  due in 2015, 2033
and 2038 fell today, which signals lower value for banks’ fixed-
income holdings.  BBVA Banco Frances SA (FRAN)  , a unit of
 Spain ’s Banco Bilbao Vizcaya Argentaria SA, dropped 0.7 percent
to 13.90 pesos.  Ledesma SAAI (LEDE AF), the Argentine sugar producer, fell
2.6 percent to 8.47 pesos. Sugar dropped to a three-week low in
New York on signs of rising supplies from  Brazil , the world’s
top exporter.  Petrobras Argentina SA (PESA)  , the Argentine subsidiary
of Brazil’s state-controlled oil producer, decreased 2.6 percent
to 8.30 pesos. Crude oil fell to a five-week low in  New York  as
a drop in U.S. personal spending signaled growth is slowing in
the world’s biggest oil-consuming country.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Bryan Gibel in New York at 
 bgibel@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
